1
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:03,320
Naree, please listen to me.

2
00:00:03,840 --> 00:00:06,640
There's nothing
between Jinchai and me anymore.

3
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:09,880
We broke up when you married him.

4
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:14,640
And I'm not pregnant with his child.

5
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,600
But right now,

6
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,560
I have nowhere to go.

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,240
-Get out.
-Please.

8
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:24,920
Get out of my room.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:26,960
No.

10
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:30,640
You're sick because of me.

11
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,119
Na.

12
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,280
Hey. You.

13
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,920
What did you do to my sister?!

14
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,240
Na. Na.

15
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:46,640
Na. Na.

16
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:49,280
Get out. Get out.

17
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:55,600
You bitch. You're dead.

18
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:03,200
Anong, why did you do that?

19
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:04,879
She's pregnant.

20
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,680
Naree.

21
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,880
Na!

22
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:46,640
Because I'm starting to suspect
it was someone inside Vanich

23
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:48,520
who sent someone to stab me.

24
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:53,440
If you say that,
I can sue you for defamation.

25
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:57,080
Go ahead.
Then I'll dig up other things too.

26
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:59,600
I didn't hire anyone to stab you.

27
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:02,720
If I were going to do it,
I'd do it myself right to your face.

28
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,680
How about right now?

29
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:08,360
Sin, what's going on?

30
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,960
I'm sorry, but I think

31
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:15,640
you're both injured right now.
Please don't start a fight.

32
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,640
Why are you staring at me?

33
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:21,120
Do you really want to stab me?

34
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:23,800
Let me warn you for the last time.

35
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:26,000
I would never do something that stupid.

36
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:29,960
Don't let me hear you say again
that I hired someone to stab you.

37
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,200
Or you'll end up worse than this.

38
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,160
Sin spoke rudely to you.

39
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:47,000
I apologize on his behalf.

40
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:49,560
Actually,

41
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,880
Sin would never harm you.

42
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,480
That's just the way he talks.

43
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,480
When we heard
that you were injured like this,

44
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,400
we were quite shocked as well.

45
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,880
Yeah, you don't have to bow to me.

46
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,760
But still,

47
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:06,480
I apologize again on Sin's behalf.

48
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:09,080
-He just has a sharp tongue.
-Yes, yes.

49
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,800
Mr. Warat.

50
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,920
Hey, I'm coming with you.

51
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:31,040
Kluay, how old are you now?

52
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:34,040
Don't you remember?
Why is your memory so short?

53
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:37,320
You said you'd believe Ms. Ampha.
and wouldn't go to Mr. Sarut's house.

54
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,200
Yes, I said I wouldn't go.

55
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,920
But how can I let you go alone?

56
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,200
If you go, I go.

57
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,920
If I go, you go.
If you don't go, I don't go.

58
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,120
But if you go, I have to go with you.

59
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,280
What are you even saying?
I have a headache.

60
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:53,520
Figure yourself out first.
Then come after me. Not yet.

61
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,360
Hey. I'm going with you.

62
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:08,640
Hello, Chairwoman.

63
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,040
-Hello.
-What did the doctor say, Arnon?

64
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,360
I'm better now.

65
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:14,000
But the doctor wants to see
if there's any internal bleeding.

66
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,400
So I'll stay one more night.

67
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,800
Who did this?

68
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,680
Why haven't they caught anyone yet?

69
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,240
They planned it very carefully.

70
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:25,600
The authorities
are investigating urgently now.

71
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,640
-Supol.
-Yes, ma'am.

72
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,200
Check who's in charge of this case.

73
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,480
-Yes, ma'am.
-Actually, that's not necessary.

74
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,360
The police

75
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,600
have already made a lot of progress.

76
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,000
Didn't you just say
there wasn't much progress?

77
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,600
There is, there is.
They've made a lot of progress.

78
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:46,000
Fine then.
If you need anything, just tell Supol.

79
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,360
Thank you.

80
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:49,000
Fortunately,

81
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,240
Warat wasn't hurt.

82
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,720
Actually, the thief's target
wasn't Mr. Warat.

83
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:58,560
What do you mean?
Then who were they trying to attack?

84
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,920
Well, actually,

85
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:07,280
it was probably just
an ordinary burglar, ma'am.

86
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,640
With the utmost respect, sir,

87
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:12,400
you said earlier that the attacker
had planned it carefully.

88
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,920
That doesn't sound like the behavior
of a typical burglar.

89
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,680
Alright.

90
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:22,520
You're still injured,
so just rest for now.

91
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:26,440
We'll talk about it later.
The police are handling it anyway.

92
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,640
Yes.

93
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:31,640
Thank you.
I know you're worried about the company.

94
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:35,680
But it wasn't appropriate
to argue like that

95
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,960
out in the open earlier.
It was embarrassing.

96
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,480
I'm sorry, Chairwoman.

97
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,200
And besides, Jirasin and Chatchai

98
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,240
are on a different level to you.

99
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,920
If you can avoid them, avoid them.

100
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,880
Don't waste time clashing with them.

101
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,720
Remember this, Arnon.

102
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,160
Just focus on doing your duty.

103
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:58,600
Everything eventually
reveals its own answer.

104
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,520
Yes, ma'am.

105
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,360
Get some rest.
I wish you a speedy recovery.

106
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,800
Thank you, ma'am.

107
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:21,280
<i>I turned my motorbike to check on her,</i>
<i>but Anong kept walking away.</i>

108
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,919
<i>So I wasn't sure if it was really her.</i>

109
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:47,520
<i>Did Anong come home with any injuries?</i>

110
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,080
Yes.

111
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:52,040
She said she had a minor accident.

112
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,840
<i>Then it probably was her.</i>

113
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,760
<i>The wound on her face</i>

114
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,080
<i>clearly looked like she'd been beaten.</i>

115
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,920
<i>Are you sure it was just an accident?</i>

116
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,920
And when you saw her,

117
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,640
did she seem scared or anything?

118
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:10,760
<i>No. She walked normally.</i>
<i>Like nothing had happened.</i>

119
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:13,040
<i>But when I saw her face, I was shocked</i>

120
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,440
<i>and wondered what had happened to her.</i>

121
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:18,360
Captain, are you free?

122
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,120
If you are, come see me.

123
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:31,600
-Hello, Mom.
-Hello.

124
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,760
Oh, you've recovered already.

125
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,760
You can sit and talk already.

126
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,920
I'll take my leave then.

127
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,400
No, it's fine. Just stay here.

128
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,880
It's unbelievable.

129
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:48,280
Two people from Vanich
falling ill at the same time like this.

130
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,280
It makes me uneasy.

131
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:54,520
I'm really fine, Mom.
It's just a coincidence.

132
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,160
I'll be able to go home soon.

133
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,080
I just visited Arnon.

134
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:01,000
He's much better now.

135
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,320
You've recovered quickly too.

136
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:04,920
Yes.

137
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:08,840
Chatchai, you as well.

138
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,960
If there's anything unfinished,

139
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:14,000
settle it quickly.

140
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,080
Right now, the board

141
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:18,640
is watching both of you closely.

142
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:21,000
Don't worry, Chairwoman.

143
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:24,720
I'll have answers for every question
once Mr. Sin returns.

144
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,000
You mean

145
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:29,000
your project

146
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,840
will continue?

147
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:33,920
What happened at the meeting that day
was an unforeseen situation.

148
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:37,680
Once I return to the office,
I'll immediately arrange another meeting.

149
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,120
No project will be suspended.

150
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,840
That's right.

151
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,440
Good.

152
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:47,680
Hearing the two of you say that
puts my mind at ease.

153
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:52,640
Once you're ready, proceed quickly.
Don't delay.

154
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,280
It will damage our credibility.

155
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,720
-Yes, Mom
-Yes, ma'am.

156
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,760
Oh? You're in such a hurry
you had to come pick it up yourself?

157
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,760
Enough talk. Hand it over.

158
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,280
How much of it do you want this time?

159
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:26,000
He insulted my nephew who wasn't involved.

160
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:26,920
He has to die.

161
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,880
Because I'm starting to suspect
it was someone inside Vanich

162
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,920
who sent someone to stab me.

163
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,760
If there are so many problems,

164
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,920
he should just die. So, it'll be over.

165
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,720
If you want someone dead,
this is the one you need.

166
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,360
You sure it can't be detected?

167
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,800
Only a god could detect it.

168
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:57,400
If it is detected,
I'll give you your money back.

169
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,560
I'll even go to prison for you.

170
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:02,680
-Don't jinx it.
-Then I'll take my leave.

171
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:17,960
Why are you pulling over here?

172
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:21,240
Did you change your mind
about going to Mr. Sarut's house?

173
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:24,640
Ms. Ampha,
Mr. Warat isn't being stubborn anymore.

174
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,000
He won't go in.

175
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:29,400
Ms. Ampha, don't listen to her.

176
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,040
Then why are you pulling over?

177
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:40,160
-You see that van?
-Yes.

178
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:44,080
That's how Mr. Sarut
usually travels around.

179
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,520
Um…

180
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,960
What exactly are you planning?

181
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,560
Can you just tell me already?
I'm tired of guessing.

182
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,080
If I told you,

183
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:56,760
it wouldn't be fun.

184
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,760
Right.

185
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,920
Does he do physical therapy here?

186
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:22,720
Yes, I think so. They do bone adjustments,

187
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,640
treat office syndrome,
and physical therapy.

188
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:29,080
Last time, you made me wear a cast
because of a torn ankle ligament, right?

189
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:32,960
Don't tell me
you're going to fake physical therapy.

190
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,880
This is the most natural way

191
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,480
to coincidentally run into Mr. Sarut.

192
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:40,200
Oh. So that's why you wouldn't tell me
where we were going.

193
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:43,160
You planned to run into Mr. Sarut here

194
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:46,200
because going to his house might not work?

195
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:48,160
You figured it out yourself.

196
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,920
Come on. Help support my arm.

197
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,880
Then I'll casually stand
at the counter and say,

198
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,880
"Hi, Mr. Sarut. Hello."

199
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,680
And slowly build
a conversation from there.

200
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,080
Come on.

201
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,400
Why do we have to
go through all this trouble?

202
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:04,800
Fine. Since we're already here,
I'm too tired to argue with you anymore.

203
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,480
-Let's go.
-Alright.

204
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:10,760
That's Mr. Arnon.

205
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,960
-Where?
-There.

206
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:17,080
That's not him.

207
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:19,520
He just happens to dress like him.
Are you alright?

208
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,880
MEDICAL FEE INQUIRIES HERE

209
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,400
Mr. Warat, I think we need to go now.

210
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,760
-Why?
-We need to hurry to Mr. Arnon.

211
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,360
Hurry.

212
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:41,880
I'm almost there. Calm down.
You'll get to eat your favorite food.

213
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,840
But Arnon, are you sure
the Chairwoman already left?

214
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:48,920
I'm not ready to meet her now.

215
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:51,800
Do you want anything else?

216
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,680
Nurse,

217
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:57,560
could you check on the patient?
Something seems to be wrong.

218
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,200
I'll call the nurse at the counter.

219
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,920
No, please.

220
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:05,720
Nurse, please check on my nephew.

221
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,600
-He's dying.
-Alright.

222
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:10,000
-I only have one nephew.
-Okay.

223
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:12,160
-I have no one else left.
-Alright.

224
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,800
ARNON KONGKWAMDEE

225
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,920
ARNON KONGKWAMDEE

226
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:30,520
LIFT OPERATION
7 PM TO 7 AM

227
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:38,040
Ma'am,

228
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:41,600
there's nothing wrong.
The patient is just sleeping normally.

229
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:44,480
Really? But I saw

230
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:48,040
his eyes roll back and he was breathing

231
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,400
like he was about to die.

232
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:53,120
I've done the initial check.
Everything is normal.

233
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:56,080
Please calm down and rest inside.

234
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,680
Thank you very much.

235
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:01,320
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

236
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,000
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed cannot…</i>

237
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,680
His phone is off.

238
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:26,320
<i>Sorry, the number…</i>

239
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,040
If the sign you mentioned

240
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,400
shows Mr. Arnon foaming at the mouth,

241
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,920
it can only mean one thing, poison.

242
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,760
Yes. Workers at my construction site

243
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,320
had exactly the same symptoms.
Just like in the sign.

244
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,560
But Mr. Arnon is in a hospital.

245
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:42,680
How could he be poisoned?

246
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,280
Unless…

247
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:49,120
Wait. What if they came back

248
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,480
to poison him and silence him?

249
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,840
Will they really go that far?

250
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:58,640
What should we do?

251
00:16:58,720 --> 00:16:59,840
<i>Sorry…</i>

252
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,680
Oh. Som.

253
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:06,599
Som told me she's going to see Mr. Arnon.

254
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:08,960
-Call her. Now.
-Yes.

255
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:18,160
Ugh, Aunt Nong.

256
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,760
When is the doctor coming?
I want to go home already.

257
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,440
Why are you in such a hurry?

258
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,720
Mrs. Wanee just came to visit.

259
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:30,160
Didn't you say
she told you to rest a bit longer?

260
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:33,600
I don't want to stay near Arnon and Warat.

261
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:39,720
You don't want to stay near Mr. Arnon?

262
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,920
Soon, you won't have to.

263
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,640
What are you saying?

264
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,880
Forget what I said.

265
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:54,160
Anyway, Mr. Arnon

266
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:58,280
does seem worrying. Honestly, I think

267
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:02,360
if there's anything you can forgive,
you should forgive him.

268
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:07,080
You're talking like he's going to die.

269
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,640
Forget what I said.

270
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,120
My battery died.

271
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,320
I just started charging it.
What is it, Kluay?

272
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,760
<i>It's urgent. If there's any medicine</i>
<i>Mr. Arnon needs to take,</i>

273
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,640
<i>stop him. Don't let him take anything.</i>

274
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:39,360
-Uh.
-Hey, what?

275
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:41,120
-Mr. Arnon.
-Mr. Warat.

276
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,960
Throw it up. Spit it out.

277
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,400
-Hey.
-What are you doing, Mr. Warat?

278
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:48,000
Throw it up, Mr. Arnon.

279
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,640
-I'm fine. Why would I throw up?
-Throw it up.

280
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:53,120
-Throw it up.
-Kluay, what's happening?

281
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:56,160
-Ouch, Mr. Warat.
-Oh.

282
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,080
Ouch.

283
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,560
-Hey.
-Ouch, Mr. Warat.

284
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,920
What are you mad at me for?

285
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,880
-Why are they shouting? It's a hospital.
-Throw it up.

286
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,280
Aunt Nong, you need to handle this for me.

287
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:07,200
-Hey.
-What's going on?

288
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,720
Or move me to another room.
I don't want to stay here.

289
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,120
I want to go home.

290
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:14,240
Calm down, Sin. I told you

291
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:17,400
you should forgive Mr. Arnon.

292
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,520
Please.

293
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,720
-Arnon, drink some water.
-Hey.

294
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,200
-No. Som, stop. Mr. Arnon.
-Hey.

295
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,480
Hold this. And spit it out.

296
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:37,280
-Spit it out. Spit it out.
-What?

297
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,120
-More. Drink more.
-Why spit it out?

298
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,520
-Spit it out.
-Sir.

299
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:42,600
-Don't swallow it.
-Can you get onto the wheelchair?

300
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,200
-Yes.
-Come on, I'll help.

301
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,960
Even if it's nothing,
you still need to get checked.

302
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:50,720
-We need to make sure.
-Who did this to me?

303
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:53,320
-Go. Stop talking.
-What if I didn't arrive in time?

304
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,840
-Who did it?
-Hurry up.

305
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:14,760
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

306
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,800
If Mr. Arnon's condition is normal,

307
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,040
it shouldn't take this long.

308
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,240
I hope so.

309
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:28,600
And we left Kluay
talking to the nurse alone.

310
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:30,280
Will she be okay?

311
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:33,400
The fact that they chose
to poison Mr. Arnon…

312
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,040
means

313
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,080
they don't dare show themselves.

314
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,360
Or maybe my suspicion is right?

315
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,400
It's just a thought.

316
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:52,000
Is this possible?

317
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:55,760
When I was rushing to see Arnon,

318
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:58,800
I suddenly heard a loud commotion.

319
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:02,080
At first, the nurse
just kept shaking her head.

320
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,440
Then Ms. Anong bowed and begged her.

321
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:07,000
She looked very pitiful.

322
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:09,880
Begging the nurse?

323
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:13,120
At first, I thought I should step in

324
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,880
or help talk to them or something.

325
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,520
But after a while,

326
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:19,160
the nurse rushed into Jirasin's room,

327
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,320
<i>and…</i>

328
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:25,600
<i>I'm not sure</i>

329
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,680
<i>if what I saw</i>

330
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,640
<i>was just me imagining it,</i>

331
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,640
<i>or it was really like that.</i>

332
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,040
<i>And what was it?</i>

333
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,960
She looked like
a completely different person.

334
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:41,320
Suddenly, she just stopped crying,
just like that.

335
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,560
But the nurse did run into Jirasin's room

336
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:47,720
like she wanted, didn't she?

337
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:53,000
But don't you think it's strange?
Think about it.

338
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,200
She ran out of the room,

339
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,120
worried sick about her nephew.

340
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,920
But once the nurse went in to check,

341
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,120
she didn't follow.

342
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:04,320
Instead, she stood by the medicine cart.

343
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:07,720
And that cart

344
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:11,480
was then pushed into Mr. Arnon's room.

345
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,560
If that's really what happened,
what's the motive?

346
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,840
That woman doesn't have any grudge
against Arnon.

347
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,280
Why would she be trying
to take Arnon's life?

348
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:30,880
I think people have
100 million reasons to kill each other.

349
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:33,880
Just being annoyed or hating
someone can be enough to kill.

350
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:37,120
Never mind Mr. Arnon,

351
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:42,440
the one who exposed her beloved nephew

352
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:46,360
for taking kickbacks in Vanich's business.

353
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,640
I think it makes sense

354
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:53,760
that Ms. Anong could be the one behind it.

355
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:59,480
I think it's getting more dangerous.

356
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,640
They're using both people and poison.

357
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,360
They'll do anything.

358
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,800
First,

359
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:09,960
we need solid information…

360
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:14,200
and we need to seal every leak.

361
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,480
It's worth doing

362
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,280
but we have to be sure first

363
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,360
that the one who did it

364
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:24,160
was Ms. Anong,

365
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:27,760
so we can respond
and deal with it the right way.

366
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,160
Wait.

367
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:34,360
Ms. Anong?

368
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:46,640
Mr. Warat?

369
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,800
-Oh, Mr. Sarut.
-Yes.

370
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:56,800
Hello.

371
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:58,280
Hello, Mr. Warat.

372
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,800
What a coincidence.

373
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:02,760
What are you doing here?

374
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:05,040
Are you not feeling well?

375
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:09,160
-Oh, well, last time…
-Yes?

376
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:11,120
I twisted my leg

377
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:14,160
-and tore my ankle ligament.
-Oh, I see.

378
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,000
It still stings a bit.

379
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:18,600
-Someone recommended this place.
-Yes.

380
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:19,640
So I thought I'd check it out.

381
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,800
You came to the right place.

382
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,120
The doctor here is excellent,

383
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,960
the equipment is modern,
and they take great care of you.

384
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:29,640
I believe your foot will get better.

385
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,160
I was really scared.

386
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,080
No need to be scared.

387
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,160
I'm such a kid.

388
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,400
This is so embarrassing.

389
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:41,400
Today,

390
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:44,120
you look relaxed. I think that's good.

391
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:47,240
I'm glad too

392
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,960
that I got to see you today, Mr. Sarut.

393
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:53,520
Yes. Well…

394
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,960
About yesterday at the hospital,

395
00:24:58,520 --> 00:25:00,920
-I'm sorry.
-Oh.

396
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,520
I misunderstood you.

397
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,960
You don't have to apologize.

398
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:07,240
Why would you?

399
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,760
Honestly,

400
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:12,440
I've never held it against you.

401
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:17,040
I…

402
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:21,160
I'm really sorry

403
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:24,720
that I misunderstood you
about so many things.

404
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:28,920
It's alright. That's normal.

405
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,280
People miscommunicate.

406
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,360
Misunderstandings happen.
It's completely normal.

407
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:37,000
I think we should

408
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:39,280
get to know each other better,

409
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:44,880
so I won't act inappropriately
to you and Ms. Anong again.

410
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:48,280
Sure. I'd be happy to.

411
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,280
Are you free tomorrow, Mr. Sarut?

412
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,080
Yes. Well…

413
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:58,080
Well, I'm

414
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,160
old already, retired too.

415
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:04,160
No kids or grandkids.
I'm free all the time.

416
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:08,600
Then shall we have dinner?

417
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,640
Wow.

418
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,960
Uh.

419
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,320
Where would be convenient for you?

420
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:19,360
Then tomorrow, can I go have dinner

421
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,680
at your house?

422
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:24,320
Great. Absolutely.
I'd be happy to welcome you.

423
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:41,040
So, Mr. Sarut doesn't suspect anything?

424
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,040
Suspect what?

425
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:45,560
He's just happy to see me.

426
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,680
And no matter what,

427
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:52,960
you're going to Mr. Sarut's house, right?

428
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:57,840
Yes. Especially
after what happened to Mr. Arnon,

429
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:02,400
I have to drag that bastard out
to punish him.

430
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,120
Mm.

431
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:06,240
But Som didn't confirm it, did she?

432
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:08,480
That Ms. Anong poisoned Mr. Arnon?

433
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:14,080
Whether it was her or not,
I have to go find out.

434
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:17,080
Even if nothing happened to Mr. Arnon,

435
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,760
I still have to find out
the thing between Ms. Anong

436
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:21,800
and my mom anyway.

437
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:23,720
Mm.

438
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:26,760
But the more I think about it,
the more confused I get.

439
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:30,880
Why is everyone suddenly
entangled in the same thing?

440
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,640
We were lucky

441
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,120
we got to Mr. Arnon in time.

442
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,480
We have to thank your vision.

443
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,760
-Mm.
-Mr. Arnon…

444
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,120
is like a friend…

445
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,440
and family to me.

446
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,360
If anyone hurts him,

447
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:01,760
it's like they're hurting me too.

448
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,040
Mm.

449
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,160
I understand

450
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:10,040
why you're this angry.

451
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:14,320
They went as far as
to the point of killing.

452
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,160
The lab said

453
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:23,400
this drug is in the same family
as herbicide,

454
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,520
but it's even stronger,

455
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:30,600
because that bastard mixed it themselves,

456
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,000
and filled the capsules themselves.

457
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,040
Whoa.

458
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:37,480
Just to silence Mr. Arnon

459
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:40,160
about the stabbing, they had to do this?

460
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,440
Exactly.

461
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:46,600
This hellish drug has no smell, no color.

462
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,720
But it doesn't take effect immediately.

463
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:52,640
It kicks in later,

464
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:56,480
causing sudden cardiac arrest
and eventually death.

465
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,000
Whoa.

466
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:02,320
If we hadn't gotten to Mr. Arnon in time,
even for a split second,

467
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:04,240
if the capsule had burst,

468
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,760
he would've…

469
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:18,680
Thank you.

470
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:22,360
I think you should eat.

471
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:25,080
I ordered something simple for you.

472
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:27,240
I'm sure you can eat it.

473
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:29,840
Wait.

474
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,840
Huh? What is it?

475
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:40,000
What if the real target

476
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:43,720
isn't Mr. Arnon, but the two of us?

477
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:47,920
Hey, aren't you overthinking this?

478
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,760
We've never had any conflict with anyone.

479
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:51,880
Why would anyone try to hurt us?

480
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,680
Don't forget.

481
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:57,440
Right now, we're witnesses
in the poisoning case involving Mr. Arnon.

482
00:29:58,360 --> 00:29:59,360
Uh…

483
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:02,960
But would someone really kill

484
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:05,320
that suddenly?

485
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:08,320
This is a restaurant.
Nothing's going to happen.

486
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,600
Hey.

487
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:12,000
They dared to do it in a hospital.

488
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:14,640
What's a restaurant compared to that?

489
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:19,840
Right now, we don't know who's who.
We can't trust anyone.

490
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,840
Don't eat it.

491
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:25,120
Does it really have to be this extreme?

492
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,440
Yes, it does.

493
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,840
Aw. Ugh.

494
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:37,960
You're not letting me eat again?

495
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,840
I know you're hungry.

496
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:50,880
I'm really mad right now.

497
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,000
Mad at me?

498
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:55,880
Mad at those people.

499
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,120
They can stop whatever they want,

500
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:00,480
but don't stop me from eating.

501
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:02,880
You know when I use my energy

502
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,720
on those signs, I have to eat.

503
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:07,000
And eat. And eat.

504
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,760
Calm down.

505
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:11,480
Here, eat mine.

506
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,120
I'm full already.

507
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:16,240
It's not about the amount.

508
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,080
It's about the vibe.

509
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:22,080
Why do I have to eat frozen food

510
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,720
in front of a fancy restaurant like this?

511
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:27,240
Why can't I sit inside
and eat properly like everyone else?

512
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,680
Come on.

513
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,360
Everything will be sorted out eventually.

514
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:34,720
Anyway,

515
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:38,080
would Ms. Anong
really hate Mr. Arnon so much

516
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:40,240
that she'd poison him to death?

517
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:43,760
Mm.

518
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:47,560
Didn't Mr. Arnon accuse Sin

519
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,440
of hiring someone to stab him?

520
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:53,920
So she kills him just to prove him right?

521
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:58,280
Yeah. Right?

522
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:00,680
That does sound strange.

523
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:06,720
I don't think this is just about Mr. Arnon

524
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,040
arguing with Jirasin.

525
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,880
Then what else could it be?

526
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:16,480
-No idea. But there's something for sure.
-Oh?

527
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:21,160
Right now, I wish I could just
teleport to Mr. Sarut

528
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:22,280
and Ms. Anong's house.

529
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:28,720
Ms. Ampha?

530
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:43,320
But I don't see Ms. Ampha anywhere.

531
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:44,800
It must be her.

532
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:48,360
It can't be anyone else.

533
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,720
But…

534
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,920
what reason would she have

535
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,120
for not wanting us
to go to Mr. Sarut's house?

536
00:32:58,200 --> 00:33:01,120
Is there another way to make her tell us?

537
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:07,120
Then we just don't go. End of story.

538
00:33:07,840 --> 00:33:09,560
I think Ms. Ampha has warned us
many times already

539
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:12,120
whenever
we're about to go to Mr. Sarut's house.

540
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,360
I've had a bad feeling about it too.

541
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:17,920
No.

542
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:21,320
The more she stops us,
the more I have to go.

543
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:25,920
I'm sure
there's something wrong with that house.

544
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:28,640
Mm.

545
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:32,520
But… what should we do then?

546
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:35,800
Ms. Ampha,

547
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,880
you have to tell us the truth.

548
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:42,000
So everything can finally end.

549
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:44,840
Please, Ms. Ampha.

550
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:57,920
Hm.

551
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,720
So good.

552
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,040
If it's not enough, you can have more.

553
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:10,600
This is delicious.
Did you cook it yourself?

554
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:12,400
Yes, I did.

555
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,560
If it's good, eat more.

556
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:18,159
I really like it.

557
00:34:18,239 --> 00:34:20,719
I've been eating
bland hospital food for days.

558
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,120
I'm sick of it.

559
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:25,440
Well, you were stabbed in the stomach.

560
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:27,360
Of course, the doctor
would make you eat light food.

561
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,440
Did the doctor say

562
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:32,880
what poison it was and how it got there?

563
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,440
Som and I

564
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,360
suspect Anong.

565
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,920
That Ms. Anong again?

566
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:41,199
What is going on here?

567
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:46,199
Yes, Mom.
I saw her messing with the medicine cart

568
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:48,520
that the nurse was taking to Arnon's room.

569
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:50,120
Hm?

570
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:53,440
If poison ended up
on the tray with the food and medicine,

571
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:54,960
there are only two possibilities.

572
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:58,160
First, the hospital staff

573
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:01,720
-put it there, which is impossible.
-Mm.

574
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:03,440
Second,

575
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,720
someone deliberately

576
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:08,040
switched the medicine with the poison.

577
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:11,120
I think it's the second one.

578
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:14,440
So it really was herbicide?

579
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:18,280
It contains compounds
from the herbicide family.

580
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:21,120
Even a tiny amount,

581
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:24,600
I guarantee that would've been
the end of Arnon the lawyer.

582
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:34,360
Fortunately,

583
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,640
Kluay and Mr. Warat got there in time

584
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:38,560
and brought him to the doctor in time.

585
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:42,560
I think this definitely wasn't the work
of an ordinary thief.

586
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:45,280
A normal thief wouldn't go this far.

587
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,960
They must have done something big.

588
00:35:48,040 --> 00:35:49,360
Once I started investigating,

589
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,640
they went this far,
even trying to kill me.

590
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,920
You have to be very careful.

591
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,560
First you were stabbed,
then you were poisoned.

592
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:03,000
I'm still not at ease.

593
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:06,560
I don't think I'm the only target.

594
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:10,040
I'm worried about you, Som,
and Ms. Kluay too.

595
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:13,200
Thank you very much, Mr. Arnon.

596
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:16,000
You've only just left the hospital

597
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,520
and haven't even rested yet.

598
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:19,840
I can rest here.

599
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,840
And I get to eat delicious food like this.

600
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,680
I don't want to bother you.

601
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,360
Oh, it's fine.

602
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,600
We don't even know who the culprit is yet.

603
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:35,200
If we stay together
and look out for each other,

604
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,960
it's probably safer.

605
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:40,720
I'll close this case as soon as possible.

606
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:52,280
Did the doctor delay your appointment?
You're late today.

607
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,960
No, just the usual schedule.

608
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:02,120
Did no one come to see me today?

609
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,000
No one.

610
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,840
Did you make an appointment with someone?

611
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:11,240
Oh.

612
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:13,200
I arranged for a repairman to come

613
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,240
to fix the house.

614
00:37:17,560 --> 00:37:18,640
No one came at all?

615
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:23,320
No. Since I came back from the hospital,

616
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:25,440
I've been sitting here the whole time.

617
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:28,040
If someone had rung the bell,

618
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:29,440
I would've heard it.

619
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:33,600
Alright. Well, if no one came,
then no one came.

620
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,040
Why would the Captain…?

621
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:44,880
Did he have an urgent matter to deal with?

622
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,280
He didn't even call.

623
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:55,640
<i>You don't want Kluay and me</i>
<i>to go to Mr. Sarut's house, do you?</i>

624
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:58,720
But I'm telling you right now.
I'm going no matter what.

625
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,200
NEXT EPISODE

626
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:01,760
<i>If there's anything</i>

627
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:04,520
<i>you want to know about Ms. Prae,</i>

628
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:07,800
if I know it, I'll answer you.

629
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,720
Ms. Mysterious?

630
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:16,040
<i>You don't need to worry.</i>

631
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:18,240
<i>That girl Kluay</i>

632
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:21,920
will never be able to have Mr. Warat.

633
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:24,920
You have a way?

634
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:27,040
<i>Promise me one thing.</i>

635
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,800
<i>If you see any strange signs,</i>

636
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,200
<i>you must tell me.</i>

637
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:57,120
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
